	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Google Tasks workflow for Alfred. Manage your tasks without leaving Alfred.

SETUP
  1. Create a Google Cloud project and enable the Tasks API
  2. Create a Desktop OAuth client and download client_secret.json
  3. Place client_secret.json in the workflow data directory:
     ~/Library/Application Support/Alfred/Workflow Data/com.rhuss.gtasks/
  4. Type "gt login" to authenticate

See the README for detailed setup instructions:
https://github.com/rhuss/alfred-google-tasks-workflow

COMMANDS

  gt login
    Authenticate with Google

  gt add Buy groceries, tomorrow
    Create a task with a due date

  gt add Call dentist, friday #Work
    Create a task in a specific list

  gt list
    Show all tasks grouped by timeframe

  gt list #Work
    Show tasks from one list only

  gt open
    Open Google Tasks in your browser

  gt logout
    Disconnect your Google account

SUPPORTED DATES
  today, tomorrow, monday through sunday,
  next week, 2026-07-15, 07-15

LISTS
  Add #ListName at the end to pick a list.
  New lists are created automatically.
  Hyphens and underscores become spaces:
  #My-List becomes "My List"</string>
